{
  "texts": [
    "However, due to the differing definitions of anomalies across series, this carries the risk of confounding the model with conflicting information when detecting anomalies online (i.e., an anomaly present in a specific curve may not necessarily be considered an anomaly in other curves).",
    "Several novel methods [28], [29] have adopted this schema driven by practical needs.",
    "Zero-shot schema.",
    "In zero-shot mode, the whole dataset is split into two disjoint subsets.",
    "One subset is employed for model training and the other is used to evaluate the detection performance."
  ]
}